abstract: Though some pundits say Jamie Dimon should be fired, JPMorgan board members and regulators disagree. | Senate leaders are near a bipartisan deal to raise the debt ceiling. | As buyout firms look to raise money, some will walk away empty-handed. | Finance may be starting to look more like a normal industry.
